INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '6dfaaf27-45e8-435c-8485-3c4378e50e40',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$FastAPI — REST Versioning, Router Structure, and OpenAPI Without the Mess$escape$,
  $escape$FastAPI's `APIRouter` with prefix-based versioning is the cleanest way to maintain multiple API versions. Mount each version as a sub-application or use `include_router` with a `/v1` prefix — both approaches expose isolated OpenAPI schemas at `/v1/openapi.json`. For true schema isolation, mount versioned `FastAPI()` instances directly: `app.mount("/v1", app_v1)`. Each sub-app gets its own `/docs` and `/openapi.json`.

For REST conventions, leverage FastAPI's response model system — `response_model=UserOut` strips internal fields and documents the schema automatically. Pair this with `status_code=status.HTTP_201_CREATED` on POST endpoints so your OpenAPI spec reflects accurate HTTP semantics.

Use `tags` on routers (not individual routes) for clean Swagger grouping. Customize `openapi_tags` at the app level to add descriptions and external docs links. For deprecating endpoints, FastAPI's `@router.get("/old", deprecated=True)` marks them in Swagger without removal. Combine `generate_unique_id_function` to control operationId naming for SDK generation — essential if you're auto-generating TypeScript or Python clients from the spec.$escape$,
  $escape$from fastapi import FastAPI, APIRouter, status
from pydantic import BaseModel

app_v1 = FastAPI(title="ByteAI API", version="1.0.0", openapi_tags=[
    {"name": "users", "description": "User operations"}
])

router = APIRouter(prefix="/users", tags=["users"])

class UserOut(BaseModel):
    id: int
    username: str

@router.post("/", response_model=UserOut, status_code=status.HTTP_201_CREATED)
async def create_user(username: str) -> UserOut:
    return UserOut(id=1, username=username)

@router.get("/legacy", deprecated=True, response_model=UserOut)
async def legacy_user() -> UserOut:
    return UserOut(id=0, username="legacy")

app_v1.include_router(router)
app = FastAPI()
app.mount("/v1", app_v1)$escape$,
  $escape$python$escape$,
